<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2911] Merge does not close input streams</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2911</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;As explained in the linked SO post: merge closes the source documents, but not the source streams.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One can call addSource() with a File object and then there would be no way for the caller to close the inputstream, so that would be a bug for sure. Not yet sure what to do when called with streams.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
